Slice beef into very thin strips. Toss beef with flour to coat. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in saucepot over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until browned, stirring often. Remove beef. Add remaining oil. Add onions and garlic. Cook over medium heat 1 minute. Add soup, water and chili powder. Heat to a boil. Return beef to saucepot. Cover and cook over low heat 1 hour. Add corn and heat through. Serve over pasta.